Before there was a printing press, there were already books. They had
to be copyied by hand, though, by copyist monks. This made books rare
and expensive, but also lended them an importance and reverence they
don't have nowadays. It also created the opportunity to treat them as
works of art. Illuminated books are a great example of it. 
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin:auto; text-align:center;&quot;&gt;
&lt;img style=&quot;width:300px;&quot; src=&quot;Illuminator/sample1.jpg&quot;&gt;
